$$
h = \sqrt{L^2 - (b/2)^2}
h^2 = L^2 - b^2/4
4h^2 + b^2 = 4L^2
$$
Need $b$ even.

Want
$$
4(b\pm 1)^2 + b^2 = 4L^2
$$
$$
4b^2 \pm 8b + 4 + b^2 = 4L^2
5b^2 \pm 8b + 4 = 4L^2
$$
$$
20k^2 \pm 16 k + 4 = 4L^2
$$
$$
5k^2 \pm 4 k + 1 = L^2
$$

Use the diophantine solver?

$(k,L) = (0,1)$ and $(k,L) = (0,-1)$
and
$$
k_{n+1} = -9 k_n - 4 k_n - 4
L_{n+1} = -20 k_n - 9 k_n - 8
$$
and
$$
k_{n+1} = -9 k_n + 4 k_n - 4
L_{n+1} = 20 k_n - 9 k_n - 8
$$
